history.content: Whether it's advisable depends on your own circumstances--if you need to graduate ASAP, for instance, and you need a couple major courses out of the way that aren't known to be super difficult, then yes. But this schedule is still really time consuming, as summer courses are 2x the work per unit of time and as a result are pretty challenging. Two techs over the summer is roughly four techs over the school year. And 4 techs during the school year is maybe advisable to those who really need to graduate soon, have a really easy time with techs, etc. Otherwise, no, it's probably not advisable. It's doable, for sure.
Is it advisable to take Data100 and CS169 together over summer (they're both in session C)?
